<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="725" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="17.[1369,2576,281,869]" pageId="17" pageNumber="725">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1372,1718,635,668]" pageId="17" pageNumber="725">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Southern Palawan Tree Squirrelis locally abundant, and considered a garden and crop pest. Forest conversion to rice paddiesis a potential threat, and although hunting is widespread, it is unlikely to be a major impact.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
